  "html_url": "https://github.com/algolia/instantsearch/issues/4953",
  "title": "In console - Error: Uncaught (in promise): Error: <attribute> is not a retrieved facet. ",
  "body": "Hello, \r\nI'm currently running Angular instantsearch on v3.0.0-beta.5 as that is the best fit for our current angular version. However, despite extending the the refinementList component with the BaseWidget, and getting it to work, there is a persistent error in the console for the facets.\r\n\r\n`Error: Uncaught (in promise): Error: <attribute> is not a retrieved facet.`\r\nThis is even though the facets are retrieved and functional to sort the data returned. My thoughts are that this error could be being thrown as the page is loading, but i'm unsure. \r\n\r\nIn the console a warning is also flagged:\r\n`angular-instantsearch.js:865 Could not find attribute [<attribute>] into hit object, will display an empty string.`\r\n\r\nHow would we go about rectifying this error?\r\n\r\nBelow are the details of the set up:\r\n\r\n**Angular CLI: 8.3.29\r\nNode: 14.17.1\r\nAngular: 8.2.14**\r\n\r\n **\"algoliasearch\": \"^3.35.1\",\r\n \"angular-instantsearch\": \"3.0.0-beta.5\",\r\n \"instantsearch.css\": \"^7.4.5\",\r\n \"instantsearch.js\": \"3.7.0\",**\r\n<img width=\"1172\" alt=\"Screenshot 2021-11-08 at 12 11 12\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/49677508/140739968-0d373f65-0556-4984-be79-74311c5f39d4.png\">\r\n\r\n**Additional**\r\nThis is how we configured the refinementList custom widget with the BaseWidget\r\n<img width=\"513\" alt=\"Screenshot 2021-11-08 at 12 45 07\" src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/49677508/140744384-44080936-379c-4a15-8d3e-aaf71ce3975b.png\">\r\n\r\n\r\n",
